.TH SYSREPORT 1 "December 2025" "sysreport 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sysreport \- comprehensive system monitoring utility for Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sysreport
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sysreport
is a comprehensive system monitoring utility that displays hardware information and real-time system utilization statistics including CPU, memory, disk, network, and process information. It supports multiple output formats, colored output with progress bars, filtering, and continuous watch mode.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Display Options
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-static
Show static hardware information only
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-dynamic
Show dynamic utilization statistics only
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
Show both static and dynamic information (default)
.SS Filtering Options
.TP
.B \-\-cpu\-only
Show only CPU information
.TP
.B \-\-memory\-only
Show only memory information
.TP
.B \-\-disk\-only
Show only disk information
.TP
.B \-\-network\-only
Show only network information
.TP
.B \-\-process\-only
Show only process information
.SS Output Format Options
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: text, json, or csv (default: text)
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Write output to FILE instead of stdout
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-color
Enable colored output (default for text format)
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable colored output
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-progress
Show progress bars for percentage values
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-timestamp
Include timestamp in output
.TP
.B \-\-alerts
Show threshold alerts and warnings
.SS Watch Mode Options
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-watch
Enable continuous monitoring mode with screen refresh
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interval " " \fISECONDS\fR
Set update interval for watch mode in seconds (default: 2)
.SH METRICS
.B sysreport
collects and displays the following system metrics:
.SS Hardware Information (Static)
.IP \(bu 2
Operating system version
.IP \(bu 2
CPU model and core count
.IP \(bu 2
Total RAM and swap memory
.IP \(bu 2
Disk partitions and total capacity
.IP \(bu 2
Network interface names
.SS Utilization Statistics (Dynamic)
.IP \(bu 2
Overall CPU usage percentage
.IP \(bu 2
Per-core CPU usage breakdown
.IP \(bu 2
Load averages (1, 5, and 15 minutes)
.IP \(bu 2
System uptime
.IP \(bu 2
CPU temperature sensors
.IP \(bu 2
RAM usage (used, available, percentage)
.IP \(bu 2
Swap usage
.IP \(bu 2
Disk usage per partition (used, available, percentage)
.IP \(bu 2
Network traffic (RX/TX bytes per interface)
.IP \(bu 2
Top 5 processes by memory usage
