.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Display all system information with default settings:
.B sysreport
.TP
Show dynamic statistics with colors and progress bars:
.B sysreport \-d \-c \-p
.TP
Watch CPU usage with 1-second updates:
.B sysreport \-\-cpu\-only \-w \-i 1
.TP
Export hardware information to JSON file:
.B sysreport \-s \-f json \-o hardware.json
.TP
Monitor memory with timestamps and alerts:
.B sysreport \-\-memory\-only \-t \-\-alerts \-w
.TP
Show all statistics with full enhancements:
.B sysreport \-a \-c \-p \-t \-\-alerts
.TP
Export current utilization to CSV:
.B sysreport \-d \-f csv \-o stats.csv
.SH OUTPUT FORMATS
.SS text (default)
Human-readable text format with optional colors, progress bars, and formatting.
.SS json
JSON format suitable for parsing by other tools or scripts. Colors are automatically disabled for JSON output.
.SS csv
Comma-separated values format suitable for spreadsheet import or data analysis. Colors are automatically disabled for CSV output.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /proc/cpuinfo
CPU information
.TP
.I /proc/meminfo
Memory information
.TP
.I /proc/stat
CPU and system statistics
.TP
.I /proc/mounts
Mounted filesystems
.TP
.I /proc/net/dev
Network interface statistics
.TP
.I /sys/class/thermal/thermal_zone*/temp
Temperature sensor data
.TP
.I /proc/*/stat
Process statistics
.TP
.I /etc/os-release
Operating system information
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error (invalid arguments, file write error, etc.)
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
The tool requires read access to /proc and /sys filesystems
.IP \(bu 2
CPU usage is calculated with a 100ms sampling interval
.IP \(bu 2
Process memory values are approximations based on resident set size
.IP \(bu 2
Temperature sensors may not be available on all systems
.IP \(bu 2
Watch mode uses ANSI escape codes for screen clearing and may not work properly in all terminal emulators
